#: ../../../release_details/9.6/vtkCellArray-generic-vtkDataArray.md:66
msgid ""
"This was done to allow, when possible, to store the given array as is "
"without needing to shallow copy it to either `vtkTypeInt32Array` or "
"`vtkTypeInt64Array`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/vtkCellArray-generic-vtkDataArray.md:69
msgid ""
"When the storage type is `Int64`, `Int32`, `FixedSizeInt64` or "
"`FixedSizeInt32` then direct access to the array is available through the "
"`Visit` functor. When the storage type is `Generic`, then the `Visit` "
"functor will provide the arrays as `vtkDataArray`, therefore the user can no "
"longer assume the arrays will be a subclass of `vtkAOSDataArrayTemplate`. To "
"solve this problem, the array access calls shown in the following `Visit` "
"functor:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/vtkCellArray-generic-vtkDataArray.md:74
msgid ""
"struct MyVisitor\n"
"{\n"
"  template <typename CellStateT>\n"
"  void operator()(CellStateT& state)\n"
"  {\n"
"    using ArrayType = typename CellStateT::ArrayType;\n"
"    using ValueType = typename CellStateT::ValueType;\n"
"    auto* conn = state.GetConnectivity();\n"
"    auto connRange = vtk::DataArrayValueRange<1>(conn);\n"
"    ValueType connValue = conn->GetValue(0);\n"
"    conn->SetValue(0, connValue);\n"
"    ValueType* connPtr = conn->GetPointer(0);\n"
"    conn->InsertNextValue(connValue);\n"
"    vtkIdType numCells = state.GetNumberOfCells();\n"
"    vtkIdType beginOffset = state.GetBeginOffset(0);\n"
"    vtkIdType endOffset = state.GetEndOffset(0);\n"
"    vtkIdType cellSize = state.GetCellSize(0);\n"
"    auto cellRange = state.GetCellRange(0);\n"
"  }\n"
"};\n"
"cells->Visit(MyVisitor{});\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/vtkCellArray-generic-vtkDataArray.md:98
msgid "should be replaced with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/vtkCellArray-generic-vtkDataArray.md:100
msgid ""
"struct MyVisitor : public vtkCellArray::DispatchUtilities\n"
"{\n"
"  template <class OffsetsT, class ConnectivityT>\n"
"  void operator()(OffsetsT* offsets, ConnectivityT* conn)\n"
"  {\n"
"    using AccessorType = vtkDataArrayAccessor<ConnectivityT>;\n"
"    using ValueType = GetAPIType<ConnectivityT>; // The result of "
"GetAPIType<OffsetsT> is the same\n"
"    auto connRange = GetRange(conn);             // or vtk::"
"DataArrayValueRange<1, vtkIdType>(conn)\n"
"    ValueType connValue = connRange[0];\n"
"    connRange[0] = connValue;\n"
"    auto connPtr = connRange.begin();\n"
"    AccessorType accessor(conn);\n"
"    accessor.InsertNext(connValue);\n"
"    vtkIdType numCells = GetNumberOfCells(offsets);\n"
"    vtkIdType beginOffset = GetBeginOffset(offsets, 0);\n"
"    vtkIdType endOffset = GetEndOffset(offsets, 0);\n"
"    vtkIdType cellSize = GetCellSize(offsets, 0);\n"
"    auto cellRange = GetCellRange(offsets, conn, 0);\n"
"  }\n"
"};\n"
"cells->Dispatch(MyVisitor{});\n"
"// or also\n"
"if (!vtkArrayDispatch::Dispatch2ByArrayWithSameValueType<vtkCellArray::"
"OffsetsArrays,\n"
"      vtkCellArray::ConnectivityArrays>::Execute(cells->GetOffsetsArray(),\n"
"      cells->GetConnectivityArray(), MyVisitor{}))\n"
"{\n"
"  MyVisitor{}(cells->GetOffsetsArray(), cells->GetConnectivityArray());\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/vtkCellArray-generic-vtkDataArray.md:131
msgid ""
"Due to this new requirement, all `Visit` functors in VTK have been updated "
"to use the new `Dispatch` API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/vtkCellArray-generic-vtkDataArray.md:133
msgid ""
"It should be noted that due to this change, offsets and connectivity arrays "
"generated by a VTKm filter can now also be stored in `vtkCellArray` as "
"`vtkmDataArray` without needing to copy the data to "
"`vtkAOSDataArrayTemplate<vtkTypeInt32>` or "
"`vtkAOSDataArrayTemplate<vtkTypeInt64>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/vtkCellArray-generic-vtkDataArray.md:137
msgid ""
"Additionally, the majority of VTK filters that were generating constant size "
"cells have been updated to use `FixedSizeInt32/64` storage type to save "
"memory."
msgstr ""

